<br>
I haven't run around on Luclin, but if it's as laggy as the rest of Norrath, it's a shame.  The graphics are nice, but with few exceptions the old PC models were more attractive.  It's too bad they allowed all the new bugs to creep in (bard songs that don't work, crashing to black screens when zoning, PC's that look like something from Star Trek, and the loss of Austrianna's shapely ass among them).  I know they felt pressure from DAoC, but unless they quickly fix these bugs, a lot of people will quit EQ. <br>
<br>
Bale <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/uaethdor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aethdor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ranja with a pet cleric</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/7/01 2:24:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongbloodsong.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=925.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Game companies starting to get on my nerves</span><hr size=1> Ok guys, sorry to burst your bubble, but something as complicated as Luclin is not a simple thing to pull off.  Compared to previous releases this one is much smoother.<br>
<br>
As for the models, not everyone likes them, but you can use the old models if you prefer them, your choice.<br>
<br>
As for testing with hardware, it's nearly impossible for them to test with even 1/10th of the configurations that are out there.  You need to remember that there is more to 'hardware compatibility' testing than just switching video cards and sound cards.  There's bios for the motherboard, and the chipset drivers alone that can cause problems, then you start throwing in different versions of windows with different things patched on it, having current drivers for motherboard, but out of date drivers for the chipset, etc, you have a situation where it's nearly impossible to test all the combinations.<br>
<br>
As for the features, well, they've delivered more than the original Luclin announcement said, but they haven't gotten everything that they have said since then.  It's a decision they have to make to be able to ship on time, would you rather have all the features possible in 4 months?  Or have what they have released, and the other things in future patches?<br>
<br>
Compared to previous launches of expansions, I think this one has been pretty good, although the pre-release of directx 8 was kind of frustrating, it ended up being my system drivers that needed to be updated after all.<br>
<br>
And don't get me started on the launch of AO, DAoC or some of the other launches I've seen.<br>
<br>
Bard songs are just destined to be bugged, it's a whole system of it's own that's got special requirements and special code to make it work.<br>
<br>
*steps off soap box* <p><img src="http://www.gusekweb.net/images/aethdorsig.gif">
